<https://w3id.org/EVI#derivedFrom> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "derivedFrom" .
<https://w3id.org/EVI#additionalDocumentation> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "additionalDocumentation" .
<https://w3id.org/EVI#directlyChallenges> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/EVI#DigitalObject> .
<https://w3id.org/EVI#directlyChallenges> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The directlyChallenges property establishes a relation between instances of DigitalObjects A and B when A asserts that B is wrong or deficient. It is non-transitive, entailing indirectlyChallenges properties on DigitalObjects supportedBy the DigitalObject it directlyChallenges, via a property chain rule." .
